Shadow Wing left so Lunarpine turned and returned to his corner. he 
lay back put his hands benieth his head and relaxed. the engine room 
was cool with the cold metal floor. just right to relaxe. "Another 
disaster diverted, whens that bird going to stop trying so hard to 
impress him?" he thought as he laid down.

--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, logomorph@h... wrote:
> ::Shadow Wing::
> 
> "I'll go and put the scanner away then."
> She turned and walked down the hall. And Shadow Wing is a dumb name 
> for an owl too, she thought.  She felt so sure he would be happy 
> about the idea of her changing forms for him.  Now he almost seamed 
> mad at her for coming up with the idea.  She shook her head and 
tried 
> not to think about it.
> 
> She put the scanner back and went back to the engine room.
> 
> 
> 
> --- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, cyberwolf4@p... wrote:
> > Lunarpine took the scanner in his hand and pressed delete.
> > 
> > "I don't want to change a friend to gain a partner, besides 
Shadow 
> > Wings a dumb name for a wolf." he handed the scanner back to 
Shadow 
> > Wing. "Next time you plan a stunt like this ask me first."
> >
